Englischer Garten.label: Englischer Garten
Englischer Garten.description: The Englischer Garten, German for "English Garden", is a large public park in the centre of Munich, Bavaria, stretching from the city centre to the northeastern city limits. Wikipedia

Kurpark, Wiesbaden.label: Kurpark, Wiesbaden
Kurpark, Wiesbaden.description: The Kurpark, German for "Spa Park", is a public park in the centre of Wiesbaden, Germany, stretching from the Wilhelmstraße to the southern borders of the district of Sonneberg and lying immediately behind the Kurhaus convention center. Wikipedia

Memento Park.label: Memento Park
Memento Park.description: Memento Park is an open air museum in Budapest, dedicated to monumental statues from Hungary's Communist period. There are statues of Lenin, Marx, and Engels, and several Hungarian Communist leaders. Wikipedia

Vondelpark.label: Vondelpark
Vondelpark.description: The Vondelpark is a public urban park of 47 hectares in Amsterdam, Netherlands. It is located in the stadsdeel Amsterdam Oud-Zuid, west from the Leidseplein and the Museumplein. Wikipedia

Sierra de Huétor.label: Sierra de Huétor
Sierra de Huétor.description:
The Sierra de Huétor is a mountain range of the Baetic System in Granada Province, Andalusia, Spain.
The range is located to the northeast of Granada city. Wikipedia
Sierra de Huétor.Address: Ctra. de Víznar a Puerto Lobo, Km.43, 18071 Víznar, Granada, Granada, Spain

National Botanic Gardens (Ireland).label: National Botanic Gardens
National Botanic Gardens (Ireland).description: The National Botanic Gardens are located in Glasnevin, 5 km north-west of Dublin city centre, Ireland. The 19.5 hectares are situated between Prospect Cemetery and the River Tolka where it forms part of that river's floodplain. Wikipedia

Warmer Damm.label: Warmer Damm
Warmer Damm.description: The Warmer Damm is a public park in the centre of Wiesbaden, Germany, stretching from the Wilhelmstraße to the southern borders of the Kurpark and lying immediately in front of the Hessian State Theater. Wikipedia

Bushy Park.label: Bushy Park
Bushy Park.description: Bushy Park is the second largest of London's Royal Parks, at 445 hectares in area, and lies immediately north of Hampton Court Palace and Hampton Court Park. Wikipedia

Green Park.label: Green Park
Green Park.description: Green Park is a park in the City of Westminster, central London. One of the Royal Parks of London, it covers 19 hectares between Hyde Park and St. James's Park. Wikipedia

Mushrif Park.label: Mushrif Park
Mushrif Park.description: Mushrif Park is 5.25 square kilometre desert-like park in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. It is located in the eastern part of the city, about 16 km from the traditional center of Dubai. Wikipedia

Parc de la Ciutadella.label: Parc de la Ciutadella
Parc de la Ciutadella.description: The Parc de la Ciutadella is a park in Ciutat Vella, Barcelona, Catalonia. After its establishment during the mid-19th century, it was for decades the only green area in the city, and hitherto of the most popular. Wikipedia

Safa Park.label: Safa Park
Safa Park.description: Safa Park is a 64 hectare urban park located in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. It is 10.53 km southwest of the traditional center of Dubai along Sheikh Zayed Road. Wikipedia
Address: Al Hadiqa St - Dubai - United Arab Emirates

Van Cortlandt Park.label: Van Cortlandt Park
Van Cortlandt Park.description: Van Cortlandt Park is a 1,146-acre park located in the Bronx in New York City. It is the third largest park in New York City, behind Pelham Bay Park and Staten Island Greenbelt. Wikipedia

New Canaan Nature Center.label: New Canaan Nature Center
New Canaan Nature Center.description: The New Canaan Nature Center is a botanical garden, arboretum and nature preserve located at 144 Oenoke Ridge, Route 124, about .25 miles north of the center of New Canaan, Connecticut. Wikipedia

Washington Square Park.label: Washington Square Park
Washington Square Park.description: Washington Square Park is one of the best-known of New York City's 1,900 public parks. At 9.75 acres, it is a landmark in the Manhattan neighborhood of Greenwich Village, as well as a meeting place and center for cultural activity. Wikipedia

Credit Island.label: Credit Island
Credit Island.description: Credit Island is an island in the Mississippi River on the south west side of Davenport, Iowa within the Quad Cities area. Its name was derived by the use of the island as an early Indian trading post. Wikipedia

Marine Exhibition Center of Punta Culebr.label: Marine Exhibition Center of Punta Culebra
Marine Exhibition Center of Punta Culebr.description: The Marine Exhibition Center of Punta Culebra or Punta Culebra Nature Center is an open-air museum located in Panama City, on one of the islands connected by the Amador Causeway. Wikipedia

United States Botanic Garden.label: United States Botanic Garden
United States Botanic Garden.description: The United States Botanic Garden is a botanic garden on the grounds of the United States Capitol in Washington, D.C., near Garfield Circle. Wikipedia

Danes Moss Nature Reserve.label: Danes Moss Nature Reserve
Danes Moss Nature Reserve.description: Danes Moss Nature Reserve is a 13.4-hectare nature reserve south of Macclesfield, Cheshire, England. A Site of Special Scientific Interest, it is managed by the Cheshire Wildlife Trust. Wikipedia

Earthplace.label: Earthplace
Earthplace.description: Earthplace, The Nature Discovery Center is a natural history museum, nature center and wildlife sanctuary located at 10 Woodside Lane in Westport, Connecticut. Wikipedia

Hancock Park.label: Hancock Park
Hancock Park.description: Hancock Park is a historic and affluent residential neighborhood in the central region of the City of Los Angeles, California. It is built around the grounds of a private golf club. Wikipedia

Patton Park Detroit.label: Patton Park Detroit
Patton Park Detroit.description: Patton Park is a 93-acre park located on the southwest side of Detroit, Michigan. The park, named for World War II legendary US military leader General George S. Patton, was dedicated in the early 1950s. Wikipedia

Riverfront Festival Plaza.label: Riverfront Festival Plaza
Riverfront Festival Plaza.description:
Riverfront Festival Plaza is a park located in downtown Windsor, Ontario, in Canada. It is located along the banks of the Detroit River, between the river and Casino Windsor.
It has over 100,000 square feet of festival space. Wikipedia

Albarregas Metropolitan Park.label: Albarregas Metropolitan Park
Albarregas Metropolitan Park.description: The Albarregas Metropolitan Park is an urban park in the city of Mérida of 612 hectares and 22 km in length running along the main course of the river Albarregas that breaks the geographical continuity ... Wikipedia
Address: Avenida Las Américas y Avenida Andrés Bello

Ayub National Park.label: Ayub National Park
Ayub National Park.description: Ayub National Park, commonly known as Ayub Park or historically Topi Rakh Park is a national park located on Jhelum road not far away from the old presidency in Rawalpindi, Pakistan. Wikipedia

De Waal Park.label: De Waal Park
De Waal Park.description:
De Waal Park was Cape Town's first and largest public park, after the Company's Gardens, when it was opened in 1895.
In 1877 the City Council of Cape Town purchased land from the Van Breda family who owned the farm Oranjezigt. Wikipedia

Fulton Park.label: Fulton Park
Fulton Park.description: Fulton Park is a park in New York named after Robert Fulton best known for launching the first commercially successful steamboat. Wikipedia

McDonnell Park.label: McDonnell Park
McDonnell Park.description: McDonnell Park is a county park in unincorporated Central St. Louis County between the cities of Overland, St. Ann, Creve Coeur and Maryland Heights. The park is named in honor of James S. McDonnell founder of McDonnell Douglas Aircraft. Wikipedia

Kotla Vijayabhaskara Reddy Botanical Gar.label: Kotla Vijayabhaskara Reddy Botanical Gardens
Kotla Vijayabhaskara Reddy Botanical Gar.description: The Kotla Vijayabhaskara Reddy Botanical Garden is a botanical garden in Hyderabad. It was developed by the Forests Department and is near the HITEC City, Madhapur, 16 kilometres from Hyderabad Railway station on the Hyderabad-Mumbai old Highway. Wikipedia

Parks and Greenways in Huntsville.label: Parks and Greenways in Huntsville
Parks and Greenways in Huntsville.description: An extension collection of parks and greenways exists in Huntsville, Alabama for the public's recreational use. Wikipedia

Naypyidaw Safari Park.label: Naypyidaw Safari Park
Naypyidaw Safari Park.description: The Naypyidaw Safari Park is a wildlife park, located in Naypyidaw, Myanmar. The park consists of a 35.1 acres Asian safari, a 3.53 acres Australian safari and a 59.64 acres African safari. Wikipedia

South Valley Park.label: South Valley Park
South Valley Park.description: South Valley Park is Jefferson County Open Space located in Jefferson County west of Ken Caryl, Colorado. The 909-acre Front Range park established in 1999 has 8 miles of hiking trails. Horse and bicycle travel is allowed on 7 miles. Wikipedia

Pauatahanui Wildlife Reserve.label: Pauatahanui Wildlife Reserve
Pauatahanui Wildlife Reserve.description:
Pauatahanui Wildlife Reserve is a wetland reserve located on the eastern edge of the Pauatahanui Inlet in Porirua, New Zealand.
The reserve contains the most significant area of saltmarsh in the lower North Island of New Zealand. Wikipedia

Three Brooks Local Nature Reserve.label: Three Brooks Local Nature Reserve
Three Brooks Local Nature Reserve.description: The Three Brooks Nature Reserve is a Local Nature Reserve of about 60 hectares in Bradley Stoke, South Gloucestershire, England. Wikipedia

Ainsworth State Park.label: Ainsworth State Park
Ainsworth State Park.description: Ainsworth State Park is a state park in eastern Multnomah County, Oregon, near Cascade Locks. It is located in the Columbia River Gorge, adjacent to the Historic Columbia River Highway. Wikipedia

Asukayama Park.label: Asukayama Park
Asukayama Park.description: Asukayama Park is a public park in Kita, Tokyo, Japan. Wikipedia

Allan Gardens.label: Allan Gardens
Allan Gardens.description: Allan Gardens is one of the oldest parks in Toronto, Ontario, Canada. It has a conservatory, a playground and two fenced off-leash areas for dogs. It is operated by Toronto Parks who also run Centennial Park Conservatory. Wikipedia

Ault Park.label: Ault Park
Ault Park.description: Ault Park is the fourth-largest park in Cincinnati at 223.949 acres, owned and operated by the Cincinnati Park Board. It lies in the Mount Lookout neighborhood on the city's east side. Wikipedia

Beaver Island State Park.label: Beaver Island State Park
Beaver Island State Park.description: Beaver Island State Park is a New York state park located on Grand Island in northwestern Erie County, New York, in the United States. Wikipedia

Big Bone Lick State Park.label: Big Bone Lick State Park
Big Bone Lick State Park.description: Big Bone Lick State Park is located at Big Bone in Boone County, Kentucky. It is located on Beaver Road and between the communities of Beaverlick and Rabbit Hash. The name of the park comes from the Pleistocene megafauna fossils found there. Wikipedia

Botanical Garden of the Ozarks.label: Botanical Garden of the Ozarks
Botanical Garden of the Ozarks.description: The Botanical Garden of the Ozarks is a botanical garden near Fayetteville, Arkansas, USA. The site is located at the border between north Fayetteville and south Springdale on Crossover Road. Wikipedia

Brickendon and Woolmers Estates.label: Brickendon and Woolmers Estates
Brickendon and Woolmers Estates.description: Brickendon Estate and Woolmers Estate near Longford, Tasmania, Australia are adjacent farming properties that date back to 1817 and a time in world history when convicts were used to provide labour to settlers in exchange for food and clothing. Wikipedia

Bradgate Park.label: Bradgate Park
Bradgate Park.description: Bradgate Park is a public park in Charnwood Forest, in Leicestershire, England, just northwest of Leicester. It covers 850 acres. The park lies between the villages of Newtown Linford, Anstey, Cropston, Woodhouse Eaves and Swithland. Wikipedia

Brown's Ferry Park (Tualatin, Oregon).label: Brown's Ferry Park
Brown's Ferry Park (Tualatin, Oregon).description: Brown's Ferry Park is a 28-acre park in the Clackamas County city of Tualatin in the U.S. state of Oregon. The park is located along the Tualatin River. Wikipedia

Beverly Beach State Park.label: Beverly Beach State Park
Beverly Beach State Park.description: Beverly Beach State Park is a state park in the U.S. state of Oregon located 5 miles north of Newport. It is a full R.V. hookup camping area with showers, bathrooms, beach access, and a meeting hall where evening interpretive programs take place. Wikipedia

Brussels Park.label: Brussels Park
Brussels Park.description: Parc de Bruxelles or Warandepark, is the largest urban public park in the center of Brussels. The area of the rectangular park is 13.1 ha. It is surrounded by the Royal Palace of Brussels, the Belgian parliament and the U.S.A. embassy. Wikipedia

Bear Creek Pioneers Park.label: Bear Creek Pioneers Park
Bear Creek Pioneers Park.description: Bear Creek Pioneers Park is a 2,154-acre park located in the U.S. city of Houston, Texas at 3535 War Memorial Drive. It is sometimes called "Harris County Bear Creek Park", or simply "Bear Creek Park." Wikipedia

Buena Vista Park.label: Buena Vista Park
Buena Vista Park.description: Buena Vista Park is a park in the Haight-Ashbury and Buena Vista Heights neighborhoods of San Francisco, California, United States. It is the oldest official park in San Francisco, established in 1867 as Hill Park, later renamed Buena Vista. Wikipedia

Byrd Park.label: Byrd Park
Byrd Park.description: Byrd Park is a public park located in Richmond, Virginia, USA, north of the James River and adjacent to Maymont. Wikipedia

Cape Arago State Park.label: Cape Arago State Park
Cape Arago State Park.description: Cape Arago State Park is a state park in the U.S. state of Oregon, administered by the Oregon Parks and Recreation Department. Wikipedia

Centennial Park (Thunder Bay).label: Centennial Park
Centennial Park (Thunder Bay).description: Developed in 1967, Centennial Park is a large park area that follows the shores of the rocky Current River in the north end of Thunder Bay, Ontario. The park was built to represent the history of logging in Port Arthur. Wikipedia

Chandler State Wayside.label: Chandler State Wayside
Chandler State Wayside.description: Chandler State Wayside is a state park in southern Oregon, U.S.. Somewhat unusual for this part of Oregon, it is covered in large Ponderosa Pine. The picnic area is near Crooked Creek which contains crayfish and rainbow trout. Wikipedia

Christie Pits.label: Christie Pits
Christie Pits.description: Christie Pits, originally Willowvale Park, is a Toronto public recreational area located at 750 Bloor Street West at Christie Street, just west of the Toronto Transit Commission Christie subway station. Wikipedia

Clapham Common.label: Clapham Common
Clapham Common.description: Clapham Common is an 89 hectares triangular area of grassland situated in south London, England. It was historically common land for the parishes of Battersea and Clapham, but was converted to parkland ... Wikipedia

Confederation Park, Calgary.label: Confederation Park, CalgaryConfederation Park Golf Course
Confederation Park, Calgary.description:
Confederation Park is an urban park in northwest Calgary, Alberta.
It is developed over an area of 400 acres, between the neighbourhoods of Mount Pleasant, Capitol Hill, Collingwood and Highland Park. Wikipedia

Emigrant Springs State Heritage Area.label: Emigrant Springs State Heritage Area
Emigrant Springs State Heritage Area.description: Emigrant Springs State Heritage Area is a state park located in central Umatilla County, Oregon, United States, approximately 15 mi southeast of Pendleton. Wikipedia

Darlington Probation Station.label: Darlington Probation Station
Darlington Probation Station.description: Darlington Probation Station was a convict penal settlement on Maria Island, Tasmania, from 1825 to 1832, then later a convict probation station during the last phase of convict management in eastern Australia. Wikipedia

Epping Forest.label: Epping Forest
Epping Forest.description: Epping Forest is an area of ancient woodland in south-east England, straddling the border between north-east Greater London and Essex. It is a former royal forest, and is managed by the City of London Corporation. Wikipedia

Fairbank Memorial Park.label: Fairbank Memorial Park
Fairbank Memorial Park.description: Fairbank Memorial Park is a park located in Toronto, Ontario, Canada. Wikipedia

Frick Park.label: Frick Park
Frick Park.description: Frick Park is the largest municipal park in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, covering 561 acres. It is one of Pittsburgh's four historic large parks. Wikipedia

Farnsworth Metropark.label: Farnsworth Metropark
Farnsworth Metropark.description: Farnsworth Metropark is a regional park located in Waterville, Ohio that is part of the Toledo Metroparks. Wikipedia

Goldendale Observatory State Park.label: Goldendale Observatory State Park
Goldendale Observatory State Park.description: Goldendale Observatory State Park is an educational facility near Goldendale, Washington. It was acquired by the state of Washington in 1980, after being operated by the Goldendale Observatory Corporation since October 13, 1973. Wikipedia
Phone: Washington State Parks and Recreation Commission

George W. Joseph State Natural Area.label: George W. Joseph State Natural Area
George W. Joseph State Natural Area.description: George W. Joseph State Natural Area is a natural area in the U.S. state of Oregon. It is located near the city of Troutdale between Latourell Falls and Guy W. Talbot State Park, and is accessible from both. Wikipedia

Grange Park (Toronto).label: Grange Park
Grange Park (Toronto).description: Grange Park is a prominent and well-used public park in downtown Toronto, Ontario, Canada, located south of the Art Gallery of Ontario, beside the Ontario College of Art and Design University, and north ... Wikipedia

Fairview Park, Dublin.label: Fairview Park, Dublin
Fairview Park, Dublin.description: Fairview Park is an urban park to the north of central Dublin, Ireland, in the district of Fairview. The park is noted for its seasonal bedding displays but also has playing fields, a children's playground and tree-lined walks. Wikipedia

Harborne Reserve.label: Harborne Reserve
Harborne Reserve.description: Harborne Reserve is a nature reserve in Harborne, Birmingham, England, operated by the West Midland Bird Club. Entry is by permit only, except on advertised open days. Wikipedia

Hanna Park.label: Hanna Park
Hanna Park.description: Kathryn Abbey Hanna Park is a 1.5-mile public beach and city park in Jacksonville, Florida. It is located at Mayport in the Jacksonville Beaches area. Wikipedia

Greater Grand Forks Greenway.label: Greater Grand Forks Greenway
Greater Grand Forks Greenway.description: The Greater Grand Forks Greenway is a huge greenway bordering the Red River and Red Lake River in the twin cities of Grand Forks, North Dakota and East Grand Forks, Minnesota. Wikipedia

Hulne Park.label: Hulne Park
Hulne Park.description:
Hulne Park is the only one remaining of the three parks that once surrounded Alnwick Castle in Northumberland, providing wood and meat for the table of the Percy family, the Dukes of Northumberland.
It is the site of Hulne Priory. Wikipedia

High Park.label: High Park
High Park.description: High Park is a municipal park in Toronto, Ontario. It spans 161 hectares, and is a mixed recreational and natural park, with sporting facilities, cultural facilities, educational facilities, gardens, playgrounds and a zoo. Wikipedia

Jamshidieh Park.label: Jamshidieh Park
Jamshidieh Park.description: Jamshidieh Park, is a park located in the neighbourhood of Niavaran at the base of Kolakchal mountain. Wikipedia

Kingdom Come State Park.label: Kingdom Come State Park
Kingdom Come State Park.description: Kingdom Come State Park is a part of Kentucky's state park system in Harlan County located atop Pine Mountain near the city of Cumberland. Wikipedia

Jingshan Park.label: Jingshan Park
Jingshan Park.description: Jingshan Park is a public park covering around a fourth of a square kilometer immediately north of the Forbidden City in Beijing, China. The focal point is the artificial hill Jingshan, literally "Prospect Hill". Wikipedia

Ladywalk Reserve.label: Ladywalk Reserve
Ladywalk Reserve.description: Ladywalk Reserve is a nature reserve on the River Tame, at its confluence with the River Blythe, at Hams Hall in north Warwickshire, England, owned by Powergen, but leased to, and operated by, the West Midland Bird Club since 1971. Wikipedia

Joe Wheeler State Park.label: Joe Wheeler State Park
Joe Wheeler State Park.description: Joe Wheeler State Park is a state park located in northwest Alabama, USA, along Wheeler Lake. The park contains 2,550 acres of land. Wikipedia

Lickey Hills Country Park.label: Lickey Hills Country Park
Lickey Hills Country Park.description: Lickey Hills Country Park is a country park in England. It is 10.3 miles south west of Birmingham and 24 miles north east of Worcester. The 524 acres park is situated just south of Rednal and close to Barnt Green. Wikipedia

Luis Muñoz Rivera Park.label: Luis Muñoz Rivera
Luis Muñoz Rivera Park.description: The Luis Muñoz Rivera Park is a 27.2 acre recreational public space located in Puerta de Tierra in San Juan, Puerto Rico. The park was named in honor of Puerto Rican statesman Luis Muñoz Rivera. Wikipedia

MacMillan Provincial Park.label: MacMillan Provincial Park
MacMillan Provincial Park.description: MacMillan Provincial Park is a 301 hectare provincial park in British Columbia, Canada. Located 25 km west of Qualicum Beach and 16 km east of Port Alberni, the park straddles Highway 4 in central Vancouver Island. Wikipedia

Luba Crater Scientific Reserve.label: Luba Crater Scientific Reserve
Luba Crater Scientific Reserve.description: The Luba Crater Scientific Reserve is a protected area of 51,000 hectares on the volcanic island of Bioko, a part of Equatorial Guinea. Wikipedia

Magnuson Park.label: Magnuson Park
Magnuson Park.description: Magnuson Park is a 350 acre park on Sand Point at Pontiac Bay, Lake Washington, in the Sand Point neighborhood of Seattle, Washington. The park is the second largest in Seattle, after 534 acre Discovery Park in Magnolia. Wikipedia

Manor Park Country Park.label: Manor Park Country Park
Manor Park Country Park.description: Manor Park Country Park is a country park in West Malling, Kent, England. The 52-acre park, formerly the private gardens of the nearby Douces Manor was purchased from the manor's owners by Kent County ... Wikipedia

Maples Rest Area.label: Maples Rest Area
Maples Rest Area.description: Maples Rest Area is a state park in the U.S. state of Oregon, administered by the Oregon Parks and Recreation Department. Wikipedia

Metro Beach Metropark.label: Metro Beach Metropark
Metro Beach Metropark.description: Lake St. Clair Metropark/Metro Beach Metropark is a 770-acre unit of the Huron-Clinton Metroparks system located roughly 20 miles northeast of downtown Detroit, Michigan in Harrison Township, Macomb County. Wikipedia

Millennium Park (Grand Rapids).label: Millennium Park
Millennium Park (Grand Rapids).description: Millennium Park is the largest urban park in West Michigan, located on the southwest side of Grand Rapids. Millennium Park connects four of the major cities in the area together, including Grand Rapids, Wyoming, Grandville, and Walker. Wikipedia

Millennium Park.label: Millennium Park
Millennium Park.description: Millennium Park is a public park located in the Loop community area of Chicago in Illinois, USA and originally intended to celebrate the millennium. Wikipedia

Morningside Park (Toronto).label: Morningside Park
Morningside Park (Toronto).description: Morningside Park is a regional park located in Scarborough, part of Toronto, Ontario, Canada. The park occupies most of the deep valley of Highland Creek where it borders the communities of West Hill and Highland Creek. Wikipedia

Mount Bonnell.label: Mount Bonnell
Mount Bonnell.description: Mount Bonnell, also known as Covert Park, is a prominent point alongside Lake Austin portion of the Colorado River in Austin, Texas. It has been a popular tourist destination since the 1850s. Wikipedia

National Memorial Arboretum.label: National Memorial Arboretum
National Memorial Arboretum.description: The National Memorial Arboretum is a national site of remembrance at Alrewas, near Lichfield, Staffordshire, England. Wikipedia
